 In the bubble leading up to the crisis, house prices increased 188% between
 1997 and 2006 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "levitin2012explaining"

\end_inset

.
 Because land prices are a major component of housing prices, generally
 believed to reflect capitalized streams of land rent, and the supply of
 land is relatively limited in the short term, land rent is the prime candidate
 for the lion's share of the house-price inflation.
\begin_inset Foot
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
A common misunderstanding of land is that, as a use value, it cannot be
 created but is instead an inherently limited 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

scarce resource
